title.narrative: IMPROVED HEALTH, NUTRITION AND Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) SERVICES

description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to water, sanitation, hygiene, nutrition and health services in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.

title.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and their families have increased access to water, sanitation, hygiene, nutrition and health services in targeted municipalities.

description.narrative: The WASH program focused on system building and reaching the affected population with required services. The WASH interventions, including provision of safe drinking water, sanitation and hygiene promotion, reached 46,408 people. In the health and nutrition sector, more than 323,795 people (against the target of 120,000) had access to essential and lifesaving Maternal, newborn and child health care and 63,457 children and PLW benefitted from nutrition interventions (against a target of 20,500), a major contribution to the prevention of morbidity and mortality. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:01/07/2020
